WEBVTT

00:12.095 --> 00:14.264
[Suzanne] <i>We are BIONA Initiative.</i>

00:14.347 --> 00:17.267
<i>Creating climate solutions</i>
<i>for a better world.</i>

00:19.978 --> 00:21.855
Hey! Where is my son?

00:21.938 --> 00:24.190
-I'm sorry, ma'am. What's your name?
-Dion!

00:24.274 --> 00:26.568
Ma'am, if you just take a seat,
I'll have someone come talk to you.

00:26.651 --> 00:29.070
-Dion!
-Ma'am.<i> </i>You can't go back there.

00:29.404 --> 00:31.573
Ma'am, you can't be back here
without an escort.

00:32.282 --> 00:33.742
-Ma'am.
-Dion!

00:34.451 --> 00:35.535
Ma'am! Stop!

00:36.036 --> 00:36.995
She's coming downstairs.

00:37.078 --> 00:38.580
-Ma'am! Stop!
-[man on radio] <i>Copy that. </i>

00:38.663 --> 00:40.081
<i>We have a code four</i>
<i>approaching level five.</i>

00:40.165 --> 00:41.124
-Di!
-[alarm blaring]

00:41.207 --> 00:43.626
-[automated voice] <i>Civilian entering L5.</i>
-She's coming down. Grab her!

00:43.710 --> 00:45.253
-Ma'am, stop!
<i>-Secure all exits.</i>

00:45.336 --> 00:46.880
-Get out of my way.
<i>-Secure all exits.</i>

00:46.963 --> 00:48.465
-Get out of my way!
-Ma'am, stop! Ma'am!

00:48.548 --> 00:49.382
[alarm continues blaring]

00:49.466 --> 00:50.341
I got her.

00:50.425 --> 00:51.718
-Stop!
-Stand down.

00:51.801 --> 00:54.637
Hey! Where is my son?

00:54.721 --> 00:55.805
[male guard] Hold your positions.

00:55.889 --> 00:56.723
[sobs]

00:58.058 --> 00:59.976
-[grunts]
-[employees gasp]

01:01.436 --> 01:04.022
[yelling] Do I have your attention now?

01:04.105 --> 01:05.190
[Nicole sobs]

01:05.273 --> 01:06.483
[employees murmuring]

01:08.818 --> 01:13.323
Bring me my child, or I swear to God,
I will tear this place up.

01:13.907 --> 01:14.783
Follow me.

01:15.575 --> 01:17.452
[upset breathing]

01:23.041 --> 01:25.710
[voices whispering indistinctly]

01:26.461 --> 01:28.171
You kidnapped my son.

01:28.254 --> 01:29.464
We rescued him.

01:29.881 --> 01:32.759
You ripped him from my arms,
put him in a van, and drove off.

01:32.842 --> 01:34.886
We were under serious time constraints.

01:34.969 --> 01:37.555
The CDC put out the call
for a level-three quarantine facility,

01:37.639 --> 01:40.016
of which, lucky for you, we are one.

01:40.100 --> 01:40.934
Lucky?

01:41.017 --> 01:44.229
He could be in a CIA black site right now,
or worse.

01:44.312 --> 01:45.146
Worse?

01:45.355 --> 01:46.356
Who are you?

01:47.690 --> 01:48.525
In here.

01:49.859 --> 01:51.111
[breathes shakily]

01:57.408 --> 01:58.451
Where is Dion?

01:58.868 --> 02:00.745
He is safe. He is fine.

02:00.829 --> 02:04.290
-Take me to him now.
-We need to have a conversation.

02:04.374 --> 02:06.417
This room is dedicated
to our weather research.

02:06.501 --> 02:08.878
We pride ourselves
on predicting wind patterns

02:09.295 --> 02:12.298
that allow us the kind of early warning
that saves lives.

02:12.799 --> 02:14.092
I don't need a tour.

02:14.634 --> 02:15.718
I need my son.

02:17.554 --> 02:18.388
[remote beeps]

02:21.182 --> 02:23.977
Oh, my God.
You left him in there all alone?

02:24.060 --> 02:27.480
He must be scared out of his mind.
Do you know anything about children?

02:27.564 --> 02:29.649
I know a few things about your child.

02:31.025 --> 02:31.860
[remote beeps]

02:36.489 --> 02:38.199
How long have you been watching us?

02:38.283 --> 02:39.868
Right after the break-in at our lab.

02:40.410 --> 02:43.538
You haven't seen a hermit crab
wandering around, by any chance?

02:44.414 --> 02:46.916
And, of course, there is the fox.

02:48.251 --> 02:50.128
I-- I don't know
what you're talking about.

02:50.211 --> 02:53.131
I assumed Pat told you
the minute he left my office, but...

02:54.132 --> 02:55.258
we can do it this way.

02:56.134 --> 02:57.552
Before Dion's visit.

02:58.636 --> 03:00.138
After Dion's visit.

03:00.555 --> 03:03.725
Your son's abilities are symbiotic
with the flora and fauna

03:03.808 --> 03:06.895
recovered from Iceland
after the aurora event.

03:07.395 --> 03:10.064
Considering Mark's intense interest
in that event,

03:10.815 --> 03:13.526
we suspect he was experiencing
anomalies himself,

03:13.610 --> 03:16.196
and it appears
that he passed them along to Dion.

03:16.696 --> 03:18.364
After Iceland, we began seeing

03:18.448 --> 03:21.034
these erratic micro storms
all over the globe.

03:21.117 --> 03:24.537
National Oceanic and Atmospheric
Administration flagged them, too.

03:24.621 --> 03:26.831
They appear and disappear quickly,

03:27.248 --> 03:28.875
leaving targeted devastation.

03:29.334 --> 03:30.168
Targeted.

03:31.127 --> 03:32.962
[Suzanne] One of these
was outside your house.

03:33.671 --> 03:35.882
Another was near your lake cabin.

03:37.592 --> 03:39.344
I don't think that's a coincidence.

03:40.178 --> 03:42.555
I think the storms are drawn to your son.

03:48.519 --> 03:50.563
-So what do you want?
-To study Dion.

03:51.397 --> 03:53.775
We need to understand
why this is happening

03:54.150 --> 03:55.276
and what he's capable of.

03:55.693 --> 03:56.527
No.

03:56.903 --> 03:58.905
Oh, I wasn't asking for permission.

03:59.948 --> 04:02.075
The CDC has him on a 72-hour hold,

04:02.450 --> 04:04.786
and that period
can be extended indefinitely

04:04.869 --> 04:06.746
if he's deemed a danger to the public.

04:06.829 --> 04:09.540
-But he's not a danger--
-There again, I wasn't asking.

04:09.624 --> 04:12.418
We have enough aberrant data
to keep him quarantined...

04:13.628 --> 04:14.629
well, forever.

04:15.129 --> 04:17.006
Which I don't want to do.

04:17.840 --> 04:21.177
But I'm not giving up
the only human specimen I have.

04:39.279 --> 04:40.905
What if you had Mark's data?

04:44.993 --> 04:45.994
[hangs up receiver]

04:47.912 --> 04:48.955
You have Mark's data?

04:49.038 --> 04:52.333
He was studying himself.
Changes to his DNA.

04:52.417 --> 04:55.920
And he kept in contact with people
who experienced the event.

04:56.337 --> 04:57.297
In exchange,

04:57.839 --> 05:00.133
you let me take Dion home now.

05:02.719 --> 05:04.971
Also, I want all of this stuff.

05:05.054 --> 05:07.181
I want to know when these storms happened,

05:07.265 --> 05:09.225
where they happened,
and if they will happen again.

05:09.309 --> 05:10.393
That's classified.

05:10.476 --> 05:12.061
Well, so is Mark's data.

05:16.858 --> 05:18.359
We'll set up a private portal.

05:18.860 --> 05:21.237
You upload your data, I'll upload mine.

05:21.321 --> 05:24.032
And one more thing.
Just stop spying on us.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.491
Not gonna happen.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.661
I could tell you that we'll stop,
but we won't,

05:28.745 --> 05:30.997
and the truth is, you don't want us to.

05:31.831 --> 05:33.875
Something dangerous is out there,

05:33.958 --> 05:35.668
and whether you believe me or not,

05:35.752 --> 05:38.212
we are trying to protect your son.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.340
I am not the enemy, Nicole.

05:41.007 --> 05:41.841
That...

05:42.592 --> 05:43.760
that is the enemy.

05:50.516 --> 05:52.352
[animal bellowing]

05:54.228 --> 05:55.146
[animal grunting]

05:57.190 --> 05:58.149
[sheep bleats]

06:01.194 --> 06:03.029
[animal grunting]

06:04.113 --> 06:05.323
[sheep bleats]

06:06.657 --> 06:08.368
[animal grunting]

06:09.452 --> 06:11.120
[animal whimpering]

06:16.501 --> 06:17.377
[sheep bleats]

06:22.590 --> 06:23.466
[Nicole] Dion.

06:23.925 --> 06:26.010
-Mom!
-Hey, Bug.

06:26.094 --> 06:27.178
She's a cat.

06:27.887 --> 06:29.055
Yes, she is.

06:29.138 --> 06:30.598
[laughing] Good job, buddy.

06:31.724 --> 06:33.309
Are you afraid of me, too?

06:34.268 --> 06:36.229
No, no, no, I just...

06:36.521 --> 06:38.523
Don't I look hilarious? I mean, come on.

06:38.606 --> 06:39.816
[Nicole laughs]

06:40.942 --> 06:41.776
No!

06:46.364 --> 06:47.281
[exhales]

06:47.824 --> 06:49.075
[sheep bleats]

06:58.709 --> 07:00.128
My butt's hanging out.

07:00.795 --> 07:01.629
[Nicole laughs]

07:02.713 --> 07:04.173
Yeah, these things are weird.

07:06.551 --> 07:07.468
I was scared.

07:09.011 --> 07:09.887
I know.

07:11.180 --> 07:14.016
But it's gonna be better now.
We're just gonna go home, okay?

07:14.100 --> 07:16.352
Where's, uh... where's your magic watch?

07:18.187 --> 07:20.690
Okay. All right, let's get you dressed.

07:22.525 --> 07:26.362
And, uh, Miss Suzanne and I,
we just have to make a little trade.

07:26.863 --> 07:29.407
All right?
And then we can get out of here.

07:29.490 --> 07:31.033
Okay? Got it?

07:39.333 --> 07:41.169
[food sizzling]

07:41.419 --> 07:43.296
["Arms Of A Woman" by Amos Lee plays]

07:45.339 --> 07:46.883
-[Nicole] Hey.
-Niki?

07:47.091 --> 07:48.342
Oh, my gosh, sweetie.

07:49.552 --> 07:50.386
How is he?

07:51.220 --> 07:52.221
-[Nicole] Tired.
-Oh.

07:54.932 --> 07:58.311
<i>♪ I am at ease ♪</i>

07:58.394 --> 07:59.937
You didn't have to come over.

08:00.021 --> 08:02.732
Are you kidding me? After what
you and little man just went through?

08:02.815 --> 08:04.650
I just... I wish you would've
called me earlier,

08:04.734 --> 08:06.486
and I'd have busted down
those doors with you.

08:06.569 --> 08:08.696
Yeah, well, you just lost your job, and...

08:09.030 --> 08:10.740
I didn't want you to get arrested, too.

08:10.823 --> 08:11.657
[chuckles]

08:14.577 --> 08:15.745
Something smells good.

08:17.205 --> 08:18.456
I made you shrimp and grits.

08:20.124 --> 08:21.626
It's after midnight. [laughs]

08:21.709 --> 08:22.793
[Kat] Are you hungry?

08:26.881 --> 08:27.715
Put him to bed.

08:27.798 --> 08:29.759
[voice breaking]
I'll... I'll fix you a plate.

08:30.718 --> 08:33.554
<i>♪ Yeah, when she wakes me ♪</i>

08:33.846 --> 08:35.598
<i>♪ She takes me ♪</i>

08:35.681 --> 08:38.601
<i>♪ Yeah, when she wakes me ♪</i>

08:38.684 --> 08:43.773
<i>♪ She takes me back home ♪</i>

08:43.856 --> 08:45.107
Hey, little Bug.

08:45.566 --> 08:48.069
<i>♪ When she wakes me ♪</i>

08:49.028 --> 08:50.738
<i>♪ She takes me ♪</i>

08:50.821 --> 08:56.118
<i>♪ Back home ♪</i>

09:02.750 --> 09:04.752
[vehicle approaching]

09:05.795 --> 09:07.880
[brakes squeaking]

09:08.756 --> 09:11.259
[dramatic music plays]

09:23.563 --> 09:24.438
[whimpering]

09:24.772 --> 09:25.815
[grunts]

09:27.400 --> 09:28.359
You need a break?

09:28.901 --> 09:31.571
-Oh, no, no. No, I'm good.
-Good answer.

09:31.946 --> 09:33.656
-[Pat exhales]
-[sheep bleats]

09:33.739 --> 09:37.034
So, she just--
She just gave all this to you?

09:37.451 --> 09:40.329
She didn't have much choice.
She wanted her son.

09:41.831 --> 09:43.541
Does she know
that you handed it off to me?

09:43.624 --> 09:44.584
Not yet.

09:45.334 --> 09:46.586
You'll tell her, I'm sure.

09:47.044 --> 09:50.339
From the number of times we've observed
you going in and out of her apartment,

09:50.423 --> 09:53.843
seems like, uh, the two of you
are pretty close.

09:55.011 --> 09:57.847
I mean, you were willing
to lose your job for her.

09:58.764 --> 10:01.183
Well, I... I care about Dion.

10:01.267 --> 10:02.101
Uh-huh.

10:02.310 --> 10:04.854
[animal grunting]

10:04.937 --> 10:08.107
I'm sorry I didn't come clean to you
about what happened.

10:08.190 --> 10:11.277
I was trying to respect Nicole's wishes.

10:11.360 --> 10:14.155
I swear it won't ever happen again.

10:14.447 --> 10:15.698
[sheep bleats]

10:16.157 --> 10:16.991
We'll see.

10:18.284 --> 10:20.661
So, what have you found?

10:21.746 --> 10:24.373
Uh, well, I've been looking
at Dion's blood work,

10:24.457 --> 10:27.418
matched it up with Mark's data
and, uh, our samples--

10:27.501 --> 10:28.336
And?

10:29.462 --> 10:32.173
And, uh, it... it's not good.

10:32.590 --> 10:36.010
It makes perfect sense why he ended up
in the hospital with a high fever.

10:36.093 --> 10:36.927
He's...

10:37.803 --> 10:39.096
He's running too hard.

10:39.180 --> 10:40.181
Expand on that.

10:40.264 --> 10:41.641
-Um...
-[animal grunting]

10:41.724 --> 10:43.809
In college, I drove this car.

10:43.893 --> 10:45.186
Um, it was a real gas guzzler,

10:45.269 --> 10:47.355
but it was the most dependable car
I ever had,

10:47.438 --> 10:49.899
as long as I didn't drive it over 55.

10:50.441 --> 10:54.445
If I even tried to push it a hair too far,
the engine would blow.

10:54.820 --> 10:58.199
The mechanic said that the car
just wasn't built to drive that hard.

10:59.241 --> 11:01.243
And that's... that's Dion.

11:01.827 --> 11:05.331
I mean, picking up Cheez Doodles
is one thing, but...

11:05.414 --> 11:08.000
if his powers get pushed too far...

11:08.876 --> 11:11.671
Like trying to cure a fox
and ending up in the hospital.

11:13.339 --> 11:14.215
Yeah.

11:17.843 --> 11:19.470
Good thing that guy wasn't sick.

11:19.553 --> 11:22.181
Something that big
probably would have killed him.

11:22.598 --> 11:23.557
[nervous exhale]

11:24.517 --> 11:25.351
Yeah.

11:26.477 --> 11:28.145
-Get some sleep.
-Yeah.

11:28.229 --> 11:29.897
[footsteps depart]

11:32.692 --> 11:34.193
-[exhales]
-[knocking]

11:47.164 --> 11:49.041
[footsteps enter]

11:57.675 --> 11:58.634
[Nicole] Um...

11:59.343 --> 12:00.845
How do you take your coffee?

12:02.179 --> 12:03.639
Cream, no sugar.

12:03.723 --> 12:06.100
You're early.
I didn't expect you until tonight.

12:06.434 --> 12:08.269
Yeah. [exhales]

12:08.728 --> 12:10.354
I had to tell you what I found.

12:11.480 --> 12:12.398
Okay.

12:14.483 --> 12:15.359
All right.

12:15.443 --> 12:16.569
[Charlotte exhales]

12:16.652 --> 12:18.320
-The farmer, Walter.
-Mm-hmm.

12:18.404 --> 12:22.032
[inhales] He, uh, got his abilities
at the same time as me and Mark.

12:22.116 --> 12:23.701
His son did, too. Brayden.

12:23.784 --> 12:24.744
[inhales]

12:24.827 --> 12:27.747
Which means he's second generation,
like Dion.

12:30.082 --> 12:30.916
Well...

12:31.709 --> 12:35.337
at least he still has his father
to help him understand things, you know.

12:35.671 --> 12:36.672
Storm took him.

12:37.047 --> 12:37.882
[Nicole] What?

12:39.258 --> 12:43.220
[stammering] When? He was alive
when Dion went to BIONA's labs.

12:43.304 --> 12:45.222
Well, he didn't stay alive very long.

12:50.019 --> 12:52.021
I can't let Dion leave this apartment.

12:52.563 --> 12:54.648
I have to go to work,
and he has to go to school.

12:54.732 --> 12:55.775
I can stay with him.

12:56.108 --> 12:58.694
-What, forever?
-Well, let's just get through today.

12:59.278 --> 13:00.196
[knocking]

13:12.291 --> 13:13.125
[Nicole] Hey.

13:13.209 --> 13:14.043
[Pat] Hey.

13:15.127 --> 13:18.297
Uh, I didn't get a call, so I'm here,

13:18.380 --> 13:22.468
just barreling through our awkward stage
to take Dion to school.

13:23.135 --> 13:25.513
I mean,
I'm not sure if he's going to school,

13:25.596 --> 13:29.558
uh, after the night he's had,
but I... I wanted to check on him.

13:29.975 --> 13:33.187
Yeah, a lot's happened since the hospital.

13:33.270 --> 13:34.104
Yeah, I know.

13:34.188 --> 13:35.022
Um...

13:35.314 --> 13:38.067
Suzanne, uh, called me in late last night,

13:38.150 --> 13:41.612
asked me to look over the data
that you gave her, the--

13:41.695 --> 13:42.988
Mark's data.

13:43.072 --> 13:45.407
So she knows you've been in on it now?

13:45.491 --> 13:47.076
Yeah. Um...

13:47.910 --> 13:51.038
What did she offer you in exchange?
Besides Dion.

13:51.121 --> 13:53.415
Uh, just maps of the storm,

13:53.499 --> 13:56.418
and, uh, her assurances
that she's on our side.

13:57.294 --> 14:00.297
Well, for what it's worth,
I actually think she is.

14:00.381 --> 14:02.424
Or at least she's not <i>not</i> on your side.

14:02.967 --> 14:05.761
The aurora event
caused some sort of extreme damage,

14:05.845 --> 14:08.681
and the land up there is literally dying.

14:08.764 --> 14:12.101
Huge crevices have opened up,
and it's spreading, so she's just...

14:12.184 --> 14:13.018
[inhales]

14:13.102 --> 14:15.145
She's trying to figure out how to stop it.

14:15.229 --> 14:17.231
Right, and she thinks
Dion can help with that.

14:17.898 --> 14:18.816
I mean, he...

14:19.108 --> 14:21.110
he reversed the disease in the fox.

14:21.193 --> 14:24.363
Maybe he can reverse
the necrosis in Iceland, I...

14:24.446 --> 14:25.489
[laughs]

14:25.573 --> 14:27.408
-You know?
-Does she really think that?

14:27.491 --> 14:29.118
[Pat] Uh, she's following the science.

14:29.201 --> 14:31.829
You know, everything that was changed
by that event,

14:32.329 --> 14:35.624
Dion, the plants, the ground, uh, Mark,

14:35.708 --> 14:36.542
it's all...

14:36.625 --> 14:38.836
all pieces of the puzzle.

14:38.919 --> 14:41.255
-And she still hates me.
-Yeah.

14:41.338 --> 14:42.214
[laughs] Yep.

14:42.298 --> 14:46.385
But, for now, I'll-- I'll be there
to watch her for you.

14:46.468 --> 14:48.596
-You don't have to do that.
-Yeah, I do.

14:49.513 --> 14:50.472
Remember, we're--

14:51.098 --> 14:52.099
Nothing's changed.

14:52.182 --> 14:55.102
We're buds, <i>amigos. </i>[chuckles]

14:58.022 --> 14:59.148
[door opens]

14:59.231 --> 15:00.232
Pat!

15:00.649 --> 15:01.650
Hey, dude.

15:02.484 --> 15:03.611
Oh!

15:03.694 --> 15:06.697
They put me in a science room like E.T.,
but I'm okay now.

15:06.780 --> 15:09.909
-That is awesome.
-So, taking me to school today?

15:10.367 --> 15:11.869
You know what? One second, honey.

15:11.952 --> 15:14.163
Um, I need to talk to him for a minute.

15:14.246 --> 15:15.164
[Pat] Yeah. Yeah.

15:15.247 --> 15:16.248
[Dion] Uh-oh.

15:17.082 --> 15:17.917
[inhales]

15:18.000 --> 15:19.376
-[door closes]
-[exhales]

15:22.212 --> 15:23.255
Hey, buddy, come.

15:23.964 --> 15:24.924
Sit down.

15:25.007 --> 15:26.425
Bah, yes.

15:27.468 --> 15:28.344
[groans]

15:28.427 --> 15:29.428
[inhales deeply]

15:29.511 --> 15:30.554
[exhales]

15:30.638 --> 15:32.222
You can't go to school today.

15:32.306 --> 15:33.140
Why not?

15:33.724 --> 15:35.517
Honey, because it's too dangerous.

15:36.060 --> 15:37.728
I have to work on my science project.

15:37.811 --> 15:40.731
-Well, some things are more important.
-Than science?

15:41.148 --> 15:42.691
-[Charlotte] Let him go to school.
-What?

15:43.275 --> 15:44.234
Yes!

15:44.318 --> 15:47.029
I'll go with him.
I'll... I'll hang with Dion all day.

15:47.571 --> 15:48.656
No.

15:48.948 --> 15:50.491
[Charlotte] Invisible, of course.

15:50.574 --> 15:52.785
But you can't tell anybody I'm there.

15:53.118 --> 15:54.453
Except Pat.

15:54.745 --> 15:56.497
Not even Pat. Nobody.

15:56.580 --> 15:57.831
Or you're not going.

15:57.915 --> 15:58.749
Okay.

15:58.832 --> 15:59.708
But what if...

15:59.792 --> 16:02.419
It'll be fine.
I'll be with him every minute.

16:02.503 --> 16:04.046
Not in the bathroom.

16:06.924 --> 16:07.967
Everything's okay.

16:08.342 --> 16:09.343
Okay.

16:09.843 --> 16:11.845
-Bye, Mom. Love you.
-Bye. Love you.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.854
[Charlotte] Don't worry. I've got it.

16:22.815 --> 16:24.692
[footsteps depart]

16:25.067 --> 16:27.152
-[indistinct chattering]
-[phones ringing]

16:34.326 --> 16:35.452
[woman] Lewis Company.

16:35.995 --> 16:37.037
What do you think?

16:37.121 --> 16:39.581
-Oh, that's fire. [laughs]
-I think you nailed it.

16:40.040 --> 16:41.208
Nicole nailed it,

16:41.291 --> 16:44.294
but I said yes to her,
so you right, I nailed it.

16:44.795 --> 16:48.048
-Girl, you killed it.
-Damn.

16:48.799 --> 16:50.384
Okay, I need one of those at my house.

16:50.467 --> 16:53.387
Take a picture and print it yourself.
I don't have an unlimited budget.

16:53.470 --> 16:56.181
-Boy! I can't with him. [laughs]
-[Rashad laughs]

16:56.265 --> 16:58.058
Okay, we're doing billboard and radio ads.

16:58.142 --> 17:00.060
I want you to work on the layout
for the playbill.

17:00.644 --> 17:02.146
Well, I want health insurance.

17:03.605 --> 17:04.523
Oh, it's like that?

17:07.860 --> 17:08.902
[Rashad] Yeah, um, uh...

17:08.986 --> 17:09.945
[scoffs]

17:10.779 --> 17:12.990
Looks like somebody's
getting promoted today.

17:15.075 --> 17:17.911
Thank you, and I'll get that to you
by the end of today.

17:17.995 --> 17:19.121
Oh, you better.

17:19.455 --> 17:21.040
And be prepared to work hard.

17:21.457 --> 17:23.083
Insurance-coverage hard.

17:25.419 --> 17:26.754
[Willa] Oh, my God. Girlfriend!

17:26.837 --> 17:28.130
-[Rashad] Come on. Yes!
-Yes!

17:28.213 --> 17:30.132
-You killed it.
-Damn.

17:30.215 --> 17:33.552
Now you're gonna tell me you're too busy
with your new promotion to meet at lunch.

17:33.635 --> 17:36.472
Are you kidding? I want to drag you
on the dance floor right now.

17:36.555 --> 17:38.932
Oh, yeah?
Think you can handle the big move?

17:39.016 --> 17:40.768
I can handle the big move.
Can you handle it?

17:41.143 --> 17:46.065
Um, are you guys still talking
about dancing? 'Cause I am confused.

17:46.148 --> 17:47.149
[Nicole laughs]

17:47.232 --> 17:48.817
-[Nicole sighs]
-[Rashad laughs]

17:50.819 --> 17:53.572
-[Rashad] I can't shut this down.
-[Willa] What is wrong with you?

17:53.655 --> 17:55.199
[Willa laughs]

17:57.201 --> 18:00.454
[Charlotte] Just go about your normal day.
Forget I'm here.

18:00.537 --> 18:02.039
You're watching everything I do.

18:02.122 --> 18:04.708
It's like I'm being haunted by a ghost
who knows my mom.

18:04.792 --> 18:08.295
[Charlotte] Well, don't do anything bad,
and you've got nothing to worry about.

18:08.378 --> 18:09.546
[Dion sighs]

18:11.006 --> 18:12.883
-Oh, no.
-Who's that?

18:13.926 --> 18:17.054
Mr. Campbell. He tried to suspend me.

18:17.429 --> 18:20.641
-[Charlotte] Why?
-Mom said he grew up with some bad ideas.

18:20.724 --> 18:21.767
[Charlotte] About what?

18:21.850 --> 18:23.685
Who people are
based on what they look like.

18:23.769 --> 18:25.687
He just assumed I was a bad kid.

18:26.105 --> 18:27.648
[Charlotte] Oh, is that right?

18:28.232 --> 18:30.442
You just walk on ahead.
Stay out of his way.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.820
I'll be right behind you.

18:48.710 --> 18:50.170
[children laugh]

18:52.756 --> 18:53.590
[school bell rings]

18:53.674 --> 18:56.218
[Charlotte] All right, come on, Dion.
Let's keep moving.

18:59.972 --> 19:03.058
There's nowhere for me to sit over there,
so I'll be here near the door.

19:03.142 --> 19:04.601
-[Esperanza giggles]
-Don't copy me.

19:04.685 --> 19:06.562
-Oh, man.
-[Charlotte] What?

19:06.895 --> 19:08.355
They're all giggly again.

19:08.647 --> 19:10.482
-[Charlotte] You jealous?
-No.

19:13.318 --> 19:14.987
Who are you talking to, weirdo?

19:19.575 --> 19:20.826
Hey, Dion, look.

19:22.369 --> 19:25.664
Ew, no way. Unicorns?
Thought we were drawing cars.

19:25.747 --> 19:27.541
Hey, can we talk about the project?

19:27.624 --> 19:31.378
Um, we were thinking
that you could make the presentation,

19:31.461 --> 19:32.838
since you're so good at science.

19:33.380 --> 19:34.631
Okay.

19:34.715 --> 19:35.716
Great.

19:35.799 --> 19:38.760
Hey, Jonathan,
let's work on that YouTube thing.

19:41.722 --> 19:43.724
[phone rings in the background]

19:44.308 --> 19:48.020
[woman] Okay, class, that's lunch.
One hour. One hour break.

19:48.103 --> 19:49.354
[indistinct chattering]

19:52.691 --> 19:55.068
["The Wire" by Fulton Lee plays]

19:55.152 --> 19:56.653
<i>♪ I might ♪</i>

19:56.987 --> 20:00.782
<i>♪ Learn to walk on my feet and ♪</i>

20:01.200 --> 20:02.743
<i>♪ I like ♪</i>

20:03.035 --> 20:06.872
<i>♪ Taking off like I'm speeding ♪</i>

20:07.122 --> 20:08.874
<i>♪ But don't mind ♪</i>

20:08.957 --> 20:12.920
<i>♪ Leading on like you'll be there ♪</i>

20:13.253 --> 20:15.714
[Charlotte] <i>Second grade is so boring.</i>

20:15.797 --> 20:17.049
Yeah, but Dion's okay?

20:17.341 --> 20:20.302
[Charlotte] <i>He's fine,</i>
<i>but how does he do this every day?</i>

20:20.719 --> 20:23.722
<i>I need a drink or something.</i>

20:23.805 --> 20:25.224
[Nicole laughs]

20:25.682 --> 20:26.934
-Ready?
-Yeah, one sec.

20:27.851 --> 20:29.186
Um... [laughs]

20:30.103 --> 20:32.481
Well, school's done at 3:00, so, um...

20:33.523 --> 20:35.651
I don't know,
brush up on your multiplication tables.

20:35.734 --> 20:37.277
[Charlotte] <i>Right. Bye.</i>

20:37.986 --> 20:38.987
[disconnects call]

20:39.363 --> 20:43.825
Uh, so I was thinking
that we could do "In The Light."

20:44.785 --> 20:45.953
[chuckles]

20:46.036 --> 20:46.870
No.

20:47.579 --> 20:50.540
-No?
-Let's do something a little different.

20:50.791 --> 20:51.750
Try to keep up.

20:51.833 --> 20:53.252
Okay. [laughs]

20:53.335 --> 20:54.253
Ready?

20:55.128 --> 20:56.129
Yeah, you're ready.

20:56.213 --> 20:57.631
["Heatwave" by Amber Mark plays]

20:57.714 --> 20:58.548
You got this.

20:59.007 --> 21:01.301
-Oh, these hips.
-Back in action, Nicole Warren.

21:02.552 --> 21:04.388
<i>♪ Oh, my, my ♪</i>

21:04.471 --> 21:05.430
Ah.

21:05.514 --> 21:08.141
<i>♪ What is this feeling in his eyes? ♪</i>

21:10.018 --> 21:12.562
<i>♪ Yes, I try ♪</i>

21:12.646 --> 21:14.982
<i>♪ To express this fire in my mind ♪</i>

21:15.065 --> 21:16.817
-[Nicole laughs]
-<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

21:17.150 --> 21:18.777
<i>♪ Need to be ♪</i>

21:18.860 --> 21:20.821
<i>♪ Where the breeze ♪</i>

21:20.904 --> 21:22.656
<i>♪ Heats my body ♪</i>

21:24.783 --> 21:26.243
<i>♪ About to freeze ♪</i>

21:26.618 --> 21:27.911
<i>♪ I need heat ♪</i>

21:28.578 --> 21:31.790
<i>♪ So just forget about where</i>
<i>We're gonna find it is ♪</i>

21:31.873 --> 21:33.083
<i>♪ Heat, heat, heat ♪</i>

21:33.166 --> 21:34.167
<i>♪ Heat ♪</i>

21:35.085 --> 21:35.919
<i>♪ Wave ♪</i>

21:36.753 --> 21:37.838
<i>♪ Hiding ♪</i>

21:38.255 --> 21:39.548
<i>♪ In the flame ♪</i>

21:40.632 --> 21:41.591
<i>♪ Heat ♪</i>

21:42.592 --> 21:43.593
<i>♪ Wave ♪</i>

21:44.303 --> 21:45.304
<i>♪ Summer ♪</i>

