<i>♪ Every day ♪</i>

21:48.140 --> 21:50.017
<i>-♪ Heat ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I want to go get away ♪</i>

21:50.100 --> 21:51.852
<i>-♪ Wave ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Feel the heat wave ♪</i>

21:51.935 --> 21:53.854
<i>-♪ Hiding ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I want to go get away ♪</i>

21:53.937 --> 21:55.897
<i>-♪ In the flame ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I want to get heat waves ♪</i>

21:55.981 --> 21:57.983
<i>-♪ Heat ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I want to go get away ♪</i>

21:58.066 --> 21:59.443
<i>-♪ Wave ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Feel the heat wave ♪</i>

21:59.526 --> 22:01.486
<i>-♪ Summer ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I want to dance the night away ♪</i>

22:01.570 --> 22:03.739
<i>-♪ Every day ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I want to feel heat waves ♪</i>

22:03.822 --> 22:05.198
<i>♪ Damn, I'm pissed ♪</i>

22:05.282 --> 22:06.992
[Nicole laughs]

22:07.075 --> 22:08.243
[Rashad laughs]

22:08.327 --> 22:09.161
You did it.

22:09.244 --> 22:10.203
[Nicole laughs]

22:10.287 --> 22:11.163
[Rashad laughs]

22:11.246 --> 22:13.457
[panting] Now, we're gonna--
We're gonna sit down.

22:13.540 --> 22:16.376
-Oh, oh, oh. You need a little breather?
-[panting]

22:16.460 --> 22:17.961
[both laugh]

22:18.045 --> 22:19.504
<i>♪ I know that it's hard to ♪</i>

22:20.047 --> 22:22.090
<i>♪ Believe I don't fear you ♪</i>

22:22.174 --> 22:23.467
["Colors" by St. Beauty plays]

22:23.550 --> 22:24.718
<i>♪ Fear you ♪</i>

22:25.761 --> 22:26.970
<i>♪ And you try to ♪</i>

22:27.637 --> 22:29.306
<i>♪ Control me ♪</i>

22:29.389 --> 22:31.308
<i>♪ Then wanna console me ♪</i>

22:32.059 --> 22:33.935
<i>♪ You don't even know me ♪</i>

22:34.686 --> 22:36.521
<i>♪ I just think you're trolling ♪</i>

22:36.605 --> 22:37.647
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

22:38.065 --> 22:39.441
<i>♪ Control me ♪</i>

22:39.858 --> 22:42.027
<i>♪ Then wanna console me ♪</i>

22:42.402 --> 22:43.820
<i>♪ You don't even know me ♪</i>

22:43.904 --> 22:45.405
Are those pork chops?

22:45.822 --> 22:46.740
Mm-hmm.

22:46.823 --> 22:50.744
We're celebrating tonight,
because your mama got a promotion.

22:50.827 --> 22:53.747
Does that mean I get to get
the Jordan 3s in white and red?

22:53.830 --> 22:55.457
[Nicole laughs]

22:56.166 --> 22:59.169
It certainly means that we get to sit down
and have a conversation about it.

22:59.252 --> 23:00.754
Yay! [laughs]

23:00.837 --> 23:01.797
Whoo-hoo!

23:03.006 --> 23:05.509
[Dion] Dance party! Whoo-hoo!

23:05.592 --> 23:07.386
-[Charlotte] Nicole.
-Yeah.

23:07.886 --> 23:09.763
May I speak to you for a minute?

23:10.055 --> 23:11.223
Uh, yeah.

23:11.848 --> 23:13.350
You wanna go say hi to Pinchy?

23:14.101 --> 23:15.143
Grown-up talk.

23:15.227 --> 23:16.103
[Nicole chuckles]

23:23.235 --> 23:24.694
Did you, uh, find something?

23:25.195 --> 23:26.530
[Charlotte sighs]

23:26.613 --> 23:27.447
Yeah.

23:28.824 --> 23:29.741
This, um...

23:31.535 --> 23:34.079
This thing is much bigger
than I ever imagined.

23:35.580 --> 23:36.456
[sighs]

23:37.457 --> 23:40.043
[inhales] I've been trying to track down
the whereabouts

23:40.127 --> 23:42.379
of some of the people on Mark's list
from the aurora event.

23:42.462 --> 23:43.338
[Nicole] Mm-hmm.

23:43.422 --> 23:45.966
Seven of them have been reported missing.

23:46.716 --> 23:48.552
And those are just the ones I found.

23:49.511 --> 23:50.595
Missing, not...

23:51.638 --> 23:53.181
dead from some freak illness?

23:53.265 --> 23:55.475
Vanished without a trace.

23:56.059 --> 23:57.269
And look at this. This is...

23:57.352 --> 24:00.147
This is the BIONA map
of where the storms have touched down.

24:00.564 --> 24:04.901
Kerry Phillips,
reported missing June 6th, 2014,

24:04.985 --> 24:06.987
-Atlanta, Georgia. Storm.
-I know that name.

24:07.070 --> 24:10.615
Right. Dr. Morton Lungstad,
Alesund, Norway.

24:10.699 --> 24:14.369
Reported missing May 22nd, 2018. Storm.

24:14.453 --> 24:15.537
[Nicole] Jill Noonan.

24:15.620 --> 24:18.707
She went missing in a freak storm
at the lake across from us.

24:19.541 --> 24:20.500
And look at this.

24:22.586 --> 24:27.424
-New Orleans, August 12th, 2017.
-[Nicole] Mark.

24:29.634 --> 24:30.635
[sighs]

24:30.719 --> 24:32.012
A storm killed them all.

24:33.472 --> 24:34.514
It hunted them.

24:37.684 --> 24:39.686
It was outside my kid's window. This...

24:40.604 --> 24:43.690
serial killer was outside my kid's window.

24:44.441 --> 24:45.734
What am I supposed to do?

24:47.444 --> 24:49.279
Run. Hide.

24:49.362 --> 24:50.989
[Nicole] I can't do that to Dion. I mean--

24:51.072 --> 24:52.657
Living life on the run, no...

24:53.074 --> 24:55.452
no home, no friends, in constant fear.

24:55.535 --> 24:56.870
What kind of life is that?

24:57.370 --> 24:58.205
Mine.

25:00.081 --> 25:01.124
I'm sorry, I didn't...

25:01.750 --> 25:03.418
I wouldn't wish this on anybody.

25:04.711 --> 25:08.089
But until we can figure out
how to stop this thing,

25:08.173 --> 25:09.674
we don't have any other choice.

25:11.009 --> 25:12.010
I mean, I was lucky.

25:12.093 --> 25:13.887
I didn't have any friends or...

25:14.930 --> 25:16.348
family that I cared about.

25:17.015 --> 25:18.266
And you call that lucky?

25:18.350 --> 25:19.351
[half-hearted laugh]

25:21.686 --> 25:23.188
I had nothing much to give up.

25:26.316 --> 25:29.152
You are gonna have a problem with that.

25:36.117 --> 25:37.035
[inhales]

25:37.661 --> 25:39.120
[sighs]

25:46.086 --> 25:47.003
Stay with us.

25:47.796 --> 25:48.630
What?

25:49.839 --> 25:50.799
We're your family.

25:52.926 --> 25:54.636
Help me protect my son.

25:56.221 --> 25:57.597
Teach him how to survive.

25:58.306 --> 26:00.934
When the time comes
and we have to run, we... we run,

26:01.017 --> 26:02.269
but until then, let's...

26:02.727 --> 26:03.812
let's stick together.

26:05.188 --> 26:06.231
Stay with us.

26:25.584 --> 26:26.835
[knocking]

26:26.918 --> 26:28.420
[Dion humming]

26:32.299 --> 26:33.925
-Good morning.
-[Nicole] Hey.

26:34.009 --> 26:34.843
Uh...

26:35.385 --> 26:37.637
-You good?
-Uh, yeah, I'll go get him.

26:38.096 --> 26:39.139
Cool, I'll just...

26:39.222 --> 26:40.056
[inhales]

26:40.849 --> 26:42.726
stand here in the hallway,

26:43.101 --> 26:44.269
like a dope.

26:44.728 --> 26:45.979
[Nicole humming]

26:47.689 --> 26:50.275
All right, Pat's here. Remember our deal?

26:50.358 --> 26:52.319
-Don't say anything about Charlotte.
-Good job.

26:52.402 --> 26:53.945
Oh, let me see your teeth.

26:55.280 --> 26:56.239
[Pat clears throat]

27:08.418 --> 27:09.252
[small gasp]

27:11.463 --> 27:12.297
[exhales]

27:15.050 --> 27:15.884
[Dion] Pat!

27:15.967 --> 27:17.719
Hey! Are you ready to go?

27:17.802 --> 27:19.262
-Let's do this thing.
-All right.

27:19.346 --> 27:21.097
-Bye, Mom.
-Have a good day, Bug.

27:21.181 --> 27:23.016
-Love you.
-[Dion] Love you, too!

27:25.769 --> 27:26.603
Hey, hey, hey.

27:28.897 --> 27:30.106
Hey, so, uh...

27:30.190 --> 27:32.359
so, who was over for breakfast
this morning?

27:33.068 --> 27:33.943
A friend.

27:35.153 --> 27:36.029
Your friend?

27:37.739 --> 27:38.782
Mom's friend.

27:39.783 --> 27:42.035
-I'm not allowed to talk about it.
-Okay.

27:45.830 --> 27:49.334
So, this friend, is it, like,
a new friend, or is it someone...

27:49.626 --> 27:51.544
I'm not asking for a name, I'm just...

27:52.587 --> 27:55.090
I'm concerned.
You have to be careful who you trust.

27:55.173 --> 27:57.342
Mom said we can trust this friend
with everything.

27:57.425 --> 27:59.511
Plus, this elevator's too slow.

28:00.345 --> 28:02.889
I'm gonna be late for school.
Meet you downstairs.

28:02.972 --> 28:04.265
Last one's a rotten egg!

28:05.100 --> 28:07.852
-[indistinct chattering]
-[phone ringing in the background]

28:10.021 --> 28:12.273
[cell phone rings]

28:13.775 --> 28:14.609
Hello.

28:15.527 --> 28:16.611
Uh, yes, I did.

28:17.987 --> 28:20.448
Yeah, I was just letting you guys know
that my friend Charlotte

28:20.532 --> 28:22.617
would be picking up Dion again
from school today.

28:22.701 --> 28:24.619
Look, I already sent one yesterday.

28:27.080 --> 28:30.125
Yeah, just email it to me,
and I will send it back to you.

28:31.710 --> 28:33.920
[telephone ringing]

28:34.003 --> 28:35.130
[woman] Lewis Company.

28:35.213 --> 28:36.423
[sighs] We've got a problem.

28:36.506 --> 28:39.759
The posters are all jacked up.
They don't match the playbills.

28:39.843 --> 28:41.594
You need to go and make this right.

28:41.845 --> 28:43.805
-[Nicole] Okay.
-[keyboard clacking]

28:43.888 --> 28:46.015
Girl, that is rude.

28:46.099 --> 28:47.350
[Nicole] I'm so sorry.

28:47.434 --> 28:49.853
I just need to fill out a form
for Dion's school again,

28:49.936 --> 28:53.815
authorizing my friend to pick him up
and... done.

28:53.898 --> 28:55.900
The original order form,
receipt, everything.

28:55.984 --> 28:59.487
Get down there now and fix this.
Materials go out tomorrow.

29:00.739 --> 29:01.614
Okay, got it.

29:05.994 --> 29:07.120
[sighs]

29:16.713 --> 29:19.299
["Best Part" by H.E.R
featuring Daniel Caesar playing]

29:20.049 --> 29:21.760
<i>♪ You don't know, babe ♪</i>

29:21.843 --> 29:23.136
[Nicole clears throat]

29:23.219 --> 29:25.263
<i>♪ When you hold me ♪</i>

29:26.222 --> 29:27.932
<i>♪ And kiss me slowly ♪</i>

29:28.016 --> 29:30.643
-You're not ditching me, are you?
-I was just trying to call you.

29:30.727 --> 29:33.521
There was a mess-up with the printer.
Kwame wants me to sort it out.

29:33.605 --> 29:35.106
And then, I got a call from the school.

29:35.190 --> 29:37.192
They didn't get
the forms I sent them, and...

29:37.275 --> 29:38.109
I can't today.

29:39.319 --> 29:40.195
Don't guilt me.

29:41.112 --> 29:43.323
-I'm not.
-I know exactly what you're thinking.

29:43.406 --> 29:44.991
Oh, so you're a mind reader now?

29:45.074 --> 29:47.368
You're thinking
this is some self-defeating BS, right?

29:47.452 --> 29:50.830
I'm keeping myself too busy.
I'm too stressed to take care of myself.

29:50.914 --> 29:51.748
I didn't say a word.

29:51.831 --> 29:54.292
And yes, maybe I should put my mask on
before assisting others,

29:54.375 --> 29:57.045
but I have responsibilities, okay, Rashad?
This is my life now.

29:57.128 --> 29:58.880
-This is the real world.
-Hey, hey, hey.

29:59.339 --> 30:01.800
I get it. Honestly, the only thing
going through my mind

30:01.883 --> 30:03.384
is that I want to dance with you.

30:03.468 --> 30:04.594
Best part of my day.

30:04.677 --> 30:07.722
<i>♪ You know that I see it ♪</i>

30:08.181 --> 30:09.474
Work on your mind-reading skills.

30:11.142 --> 30:12.602
See you tomorrow, hopefully.

30:12.685 --> 30:14.354
<i>♪ Where you go, I'll follow ♪</i>

30:14.437 --> 30:16.564
<i>♪ No matter how far ♪</i>

30:16.648 --> 30:17.482
Hey.

30:17.565 --> 30:20.485
<i>♪ If life is a movie ♪</i>

30:20.568 --> 30:21.569
One minute.

30:21.653 --> 30:23.571
<i>♪ Oh, you're the best part ♪</i>

30:23.655 --> 30:24.489
Hey.

30:24.572 --> 30:26.825
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

30:27.575 --> 30:30.453
<i>♪ You're the best part ♪</i>

30:30.870 --> 30:34.165
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

30:34.833 --> 30:36.835
<i>♪ Best part ♪</i>

30:37.168 --> 30:39.128
<i>♪ It's the sunrise ♪</i>

30:40.213 --> 30:42.632
<i>♪ And those brown eyes, yes ♪</i>

30:43.508 --> 30:47.637
<i>♪ You're the one that I desire ♪</i>

30:49.639 --> 30:51.724
<i>♪ When we wake up ♪</i>

30:52.767 --> 30:55.228
<i>♪ And then, we make love ♪</i>

30:56.563 --> 30:58.398
<i>♪ It makes me feel so nice ♪</i>

30:58.481 --> 30:59.315
[clears throat]

31:01.609 --> 31:04.821
<i>♪ You're my water</i>
<i>When I'm stuck in the desert ♪</i>

31:05.405 --> 31:06.990
[Nicole] Ooh. [giggles]

31:08.950 --> 31:12.537
<i>♪ You're the sunshine on my life ♪</i>

31:12.954 --> 31:14.080
[Nicole giggles]

31:15.206 --> 31:18.084
<i>♪ I just wanna see how ♪</i>

31:18.167 --> 31:20.837
<i>♪ Beautiful you are ♪</i>

31:21.588 --> 31:24.591
<i>-♪ You know that I see it ♪</i>
-[Rashad laughs]

31:24.799 --> 31:27.802
<i>♪ I know you're a star ♪</i>

31:28.094 --> 31:31.055
<i>♪ Where you go, I'll follow ♪</i>

31:31.264 --> 31:33.933
<i>-♪ No matter how far ♪</i>
<i>-</i>[Nicole laughs]

31:34.392 --> 31:36.144
<i>♪ If life is a movie ♪</i>

31:36.227 --> 31:37.478
[Rashad and Nicole laugh]

31:37.562 --> 31:40.899
<i>-♪ Then you're the best part ♪</i>
-[Nicole laughs]

31:41.232 --> 31:43.943
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

31:44.027 --> 31:47.363
<i>♪ You're the best part ♪</i>

31:47.447 --> 31:48.281
[Mr. Fry] Okay.

31:48.823 --> 31:49.657
This...

31:50.325 --> 31:51.576
almost looks ready.

31:51.659 --> 31:52.869
How you doing over here?

31:53.411 --> 31:55.288
Okay. I like that.

31:56.164 --> 31:57.707
How's Team Weather Control doing?

31:57.790 --> 31:59.584
Me and Esperanza are doing great.

32:01.586 --> 32:04.005
Esperanza created
a simulated storm in a jar.

32:04.088 --> 32:06.174
I saw it on YouTube,
and Jonathan helped me.

32:06.257 --> 32:07.634
Storm in a jar.

32:07.926 --> 32:08.801
[laughs]

32:08.885 --> 32:10.136
I love it. What else?

32:10.595 --> 32:12.472
-I have a speech.
-Yeah?

32:13.056 --> 32:13.973
Let's hear it.

32:16.809 --> 32:17.685
[clears throat]

32:18.144 --> 32:21.397
Storms are created when a warm front
meets a cold front.

32:21.898 --> 32:24.567
The more difference there is
between these two temperatures,

32:24.651 --> 32:26.069
the stronger the storm.

32:26.152 --> 32:27.570
You've done your research.

32:27.654 --> 32:28.696
He's not done.

32:28.780 --> 32:29.739
[inhales, exhales]

32:29.822 --> 32:31.282
Storms kill people.

32:31.783 --> 32:32.617
My dad...

32:33.451 --> 32:34.494
Um...

32:34.869 --> 32:39.666
my dad worked at BIONA to find a way
to stop storms in the future,

32:40.291 --> 32:44.295
but what if I told you that there's a way
to stop a storm right now?

32:44.754 --> 32:49.968
Ladies and gentlemen,
introducing the storm extinguisher!

32:50.051 --> 32:53.096
And that's when Jonathan comes in
with the storm extinguisher.

32:54.263 --> 32:55.098
Where is it?

32:55.640 --> 32:57.058
It's not... I mean...

32:59.727 --> 33:01.020
I didn't finish it.

33:01.104 --> 33:03.648
Well, today's the day
for me to approve your projects.

33:03.731 --> 33:05.858
If you didn't do the assignment,
then I don't know how--

33:05.942 --> 33:07.819
He did! Show him.

33:08.695 --> 33:10.905
It's dumb. I didn't know what to do.

33:18.788 --> 33:19.789
What's the hose for?

33:20.206 --> 33:21.708
Uh, you know, the, uh...

33:21.791 --> 33:23.876
-Um...
-Cold air...

33:23.960 --> 33:25.795
from a liquid nitrogen canister.

33:25.878 --> 33:27.714
[stammers] Yeah, the cold air stuff.

33:28.172 --> 33:29.841
-It, uh...
-[Dion groans]

33:29.924 --> 33:33.177
Changes the temperature of the storm
and takes away its power.

33:33.803 --> 33:34.637
Okay.

33:35.430 --> 33:36.889
Wait. You... you made this?

33:37.181 --> 33:38.016
Yeah.

33:38.099 --> 33:39.851
-And the rubber straps?
-[Jonathan] Well...

33:42.103 --> 33:44.480
I figured if there's a storm,
there's gonna be some lightning,

33:44.564 --> 33:47.567
and rubber stops lightning, I think.

33:47.900 --> 33:49.027
[Mr. Fry laughs]

33:49.110 --> 33:51.195
It's a little more complicated than that.

33:51.404 --> 33:53.906
No, but keep doing research.

33:53.990 --> 33:54.949
Good thinking, though.

33:55.033 --> 33:56.117
When will it be finished?

33:56.200 --> 33:58.411
Today, after school. Promise.

33:58.661 --> 33:59.495
Okay.

33:59.746 --> 34:02.665
You've got until tomorrow, okay?

34:02.749 --> 34:04.625
[school bell rings]

34:07.962 --> 34:10.673
-I can't come over after school today.
-You don't need to.

34:10.757 --> 34:13.593
Jonathan and I are gonna play Zelda
after school anyway.

34:14.469 --> 34:15.303
What?

34:16.054 --> 34:17.889
We'll finish
his part of the project first.

34:18.306 --> 34:20.308
-You're playing Zelda?
-[Esperanza] Yeah.

34:20.683 --> 34:22.935
I would've invited you,
but you hate Zelda.

34:23.019 --> 34:24.979
I don't hate Zelda.

34:25.063 --> 34:27.231
Hey, Jonathan. Come here.

34:29.609 --> 34:30.860
[Esperanza] What do they want?

34:30.943 --> 34:33.780
They're so mean to him.
I don't even know why he talks to them.

34:33.863 --> 34:34.781
They're his friends.

34:34.864 --> 34:36.908
Uh, not really.
They're being nice to him one day,

34:36.991 --> 34:38.743
but then, the next,
they're making fun of him.

34:38.826 --> 34:41.162
Where he lives, his dad...

34:41.662 --> 34:42.997
Hey, what's up, guys?

34:43.081 --> 34:44.957
Uh, I'm gonna go to the skate park
with the guys.

34:45.041 --> 34:48.086
But we promised
we would finish the Storm Killer!

34:48.169 --> 34:51.005
-You coming or not?
-I'm not waiting.

34:53.424 --> 34:54.842
What about the project?

34:55.676 --> 34:57.929
You do your part. Don't worry about mine.

34:58.012 --> 35:00.014
Hey, it's due tomorrow.
It's our project, too.

35:00.431 --> 35:02.266
-It's okay, I'll do it.
-[Dion] What?

35:02.475 --> 35:03.643
-[Jonathan] Hey.
-[Dion grunts]

35:03.726 --> 35:05.103
She'll do it better anyway.

35:09.107 --> 35:09.941
Hey.

35:10.358 --> 35:11.275
Come with me.

35:11.859 --> 35:14.654
Forget about Jonathan.
I wanna show you something fun.

35:15.446 --> 35:16.280
Quick.

35:23.412 --> 35:24.664
[electricity crackles]

35:24.747 --> 35:25.748
What are you doing?

35:26.165 --> 35:27.250
Shh.

35:28.668 --> 35:29.669
What are you doing?

35:30.419 --> 35:31.921
Who needs skateboards when...

35:32.630 --> 35:34.006
you can fly?

35:34.674 --> 35:37.051
Dion, put me down!

35:37.844 --> 35:39.971
I used to only be able to lift
Froot Loops.

35:40.346 --> 35:41.931
Put me down!

35:42.014 --> 35:44.642
Wait! Here comes the best part.
You're gonna miss it.

35:46.811 --> 35:49.397
Wait. What are you doing with my legs?

35:49.772 --> 35:50.898
Put me down!

35:51.691 --> 35:52.692
Dion!

35:59.448 --> 36:00.616
Why did you do that?

36:01.033 --> 36:03.161
-Why are you mad?
-You took me out of my chair.

36:03.244 --> 36:06.497
You lifted me out of my chair.

36:06.831 --> 36:08.624
Why would you do that?

36:09.167 --> 36:10.793
-I wanted you to--
-Walk?

36:11.711 --> 36:12.962
Yes.

36:17.008 --> 36:18.009
Open the door.

36:21.762 --> 36:22.763
Thank you.

36:31.230 --> 36:33.441
Hey. What are you doing here?

36:35.401 --> 36:36.319
Uh...

36:37.737 --> 36:39.655
[voice breaking]
I told myself, you know...

36:41.199 --> 36:43.159
if you let something go
and it's meant to be,

36:43.242 --> 36:44.744
it'll come back to you.

36:45.912 --> 36:47.455
I'm so stupid.

36:49.123 --> 36:49.957
Um...

36:50.917 --> 36:52.835
Pat, I don't really know
what's going on with you,

36:52.919 --> 36:56.464
but I'm running late to the printer,
so can we just talk about this later?

36:56.839 --> 36:58.633
-Um, no.
-[Nicole] No?

36:59.759 --> 37:00.593
No.

37:01.010 --> 37:03.346
I'm, uh... I'm so tired of this.

37:04.388 --> 37:05.848
Whenever you need me, I'm there.

37:05.932 --> 37:08.684
To take Dion to school, for... for pizza.

37:08.768 --> 37:11.854
You ask and I drop everything for you,

37:11.938 --> 37:14.232
and I'm there
with a big old smile on my face.

37:15.399 --> 37:17.443
Why are you doing this now?

37:18.819 --> 37:22.114
Uh, I think you are
taking advantage of me.

37:22.990 --> 37:24.325
Because you know that I...

37:27.870 --> 37:30.164
Because you know
that I have feelings for you.

37:38.714 --> 37:39.799
I'm sorry, I...

37:41.467 --> 37:42.468
I never meant to--

37:43.261 --> 37:44.095
But...

37:44.762 --> 37:46.472
you're right. I, um...

37:47.765 --> 37:50.226
I shouldn't have continued
to lean on you like that.

37:50.309 --> 37:52.853
So, are you...
are you, uh, seeing that guy?

37:56.482 --> 37:57.358
Excuse me?

37:58.943 --> 37:59.944
[deep breath]

38:00.486 --> 38:04.490
This morning when I picked Dion up,
there was an extra plate at the table.

38:04.573 --> 38:06.492
Was it him? Or, like...

38:11.664 --> 38:14.166
That's none of your business.

38:14.583 --> 38:15.459
Really?

38:15.543 --> 38:16.752
-[Nicole] Yes.
-Hmm.

38:17.878 --> 38:21.340
And I appreciate everything
that you've done for me and Dion, but...

38:22.591 --> 38:24.593
who I have breakfast with,

38:25.136 --> 38:27.888
who I whatever with,
it's... it's none of your business.

38:27.972 --> 38:30.766
Well, but see, the thing is Nicole,
you are my business.

38:31.559 --> 38:33.519
Okay? I've been keeping your secrets.

38:33.894 --> 38:35.771
I've been risking my job for you.

38:35.855 --> 38:37.315
And you... you... [upset laugh]

38:37.398 --> 38:39.817
[sniffs] You let me think
I had a shot, I guess,

38:39.900 --> 38:41.193
so I could just keep on being

38:41.277 --> 38:43.321
-your pathetic little errand boy.
-Okay, um...

38:43.821 --> 38:44.947
This conversation's over.

38:45.031 --> 38:48.034
Actually, um...
I have to get back to work.

38:48.326 --> 38:50.077
Oh, all right.
Well, we'll finish it tonight

38:50.161 --> 38:51.912
when I bring Dion home.

38:51.996 --> 38:55.291
You know what? You don't have to,
because I have it taken care of.

38:55.750 --> 38:56.584
What?

38:56.667 --> 38:59.628
And you know,  I think maybe
we should just... take a break.

38:59.712 --> 39:00.546
[scoffs]

39:01.005 --> 39:02.214
Take a break. From what?

39:02.298 --> 39:04.759
From you spending time with Dion, with me.

39:09.597 --> 39:10.431
Well...

39:10.514 --> 39:11.349
[scoffs]

39:11.849 --> 39:13.768
You're not keeping me from Dion.

39:15.186 --> 39:16.812
-Excuse me?
-[Pat] He loves me.

39:16.896 --> 39:18.856
Hell, I spend more time with him than you.

39:21.192 --> 39:23.361
This conversation is so over.

39:23.694 --> 39:26.197
You stay away from me,
and you stay away from Dion.

39:30.951 --> 39:32.661
[students chattering indistinctly]

39:38.417 --> 39:41.504
I don't get it. Why is Esperanza so mad?

39:41.587 --> 39:42.421
Oh.

39:43.047 --> 39:44.840
Let us get out of this place,

39:45.091 --> 39:47.885
away from all these people,

39:47.968 --> 39:51.764
and then we will discuss
your disaster with Esperanza.

39:51.847 --> 39:53.265
[cell phone beeping]

39:53.682 --> 39:55.643
-Hey.
-Hey, is Dion with you?

39:55.726 --> 39:57.061
Yes, I just picked him up.

39:57.144 --> 40:01.524
Okay, don't tell him, but Pat and I
just got into the weirdest fight.

40:01.607 --> 40:03.734
[Charlotte] <i>Uh, want me to do a thing?</i>

40:03.818 --> 40:05.861
One zap and he'll never pee right again.

40:05.945 --> 40:07.321
No... [sighs] It's fine.

40:07.405 --> 40:10.658
-He just needs to stay away and cool off.
-[Charlotte] <i>Well, we're on our way home.</i>

40:10.741 --> 40:12.701
-[Dion] <i>Can you take me to Esperanza's?</i>
-No.

40:12.785 --> 40:14.328
No. Hey, are you okay?

40:14.412 --> 40:15.496
[Nicole] <i>No, I'm mad!</i>

40:15.579 --> 40:18.040
He acted like he was entitled
to something from me

40:18.124 --> 40:20.000
and accused me of seeing someone
behind his back.

40:20.084 --> 40:22.837
<i>Is his back even relevant?</i>
<i>His back has nothing to do with me.</i>

40:22.920 --> 40:25.589
Look, you know,
you're getting a little lost in this.

40:25.673 --> 40:28.092
Look, I tried to be honest with him.
I tried, at least,

40:28.175 --> 40:31.220
and he still came away from it
expecting something from me.

40:31.303 --> 40:34.640
I really need to get out of here.
Can we talk about this later?

40:35.182 --> 40:38.894
Just don't let Pat talk to him, okay?
And... and I'll see you guys at home.

40:39.728 --> 40:40.729
[disconnects call]

40:44.442 --> 40:45.776
[Dion] It wasn't that bad.

40:46.110 --> 40:47.945
[Charlotte] I was there. It was bad.

40:48.237 --> 40:50.197
If I were in a wheelchair,
I would want to fly.

40:50.281 --> 40:52.283
Well, you are not Esperanza.

40:52.366 --> 40:54.118
Everybody wants to fly.

40:54.201 --> 40:56.620
I think you've just proven
that that is not true.

40:57.413 --> 40:58.539
[Charlotte sighs]

40:58.831 --> 41:00.207
What do you know about her?

41:01.625 --> 41:03.127
Well, why is she in the chair?

41:03.794 --> 41:06.547
How long has she been in the chair?
Has she ever walked?

41:08.674 --> 41:10.342
Dude, you've been friends with her
how long?

41:10.426 --> 41:13.304
And you've never talked about it?
You've never even asked?

41:14.430 --> 41:16.265
I don't think about it. It's just--

41:16.891 --> 41:18.267
It's Esperanza.

41:19.852 --> 41:23.272
Now, that, I think she would want
to hear you say.

41:25.608 --> 41:27.151
[man coughing]

41:27.902 --> 41:29.987
[coughing continues]

41:31.572 --> 41:33.199
-[coughing]
-[Charlotte] Um...

41:33.282 --> 41:35.534
Why don't you go inside,  and...

41:36.160 --> 41:38.037
I will join you in a few minutes.

41:38.120 --> 41:41.248
-[Dion] Can I FaceTime with Esperanza?
-[Charlotte] Absolutely.

41:42.374 --> 41:43.250
[exhales]

41:48.255 --> 41:49.215
[exhales]

41:49.507 --> 41:50.341
[sniffs]

41:50.591 --> 41:52.134
-Excuse me.
-Pat, right?

41:53.594 --> 41:54.845
I'm a friend of Nicole's.

41:55.930 --> 41:58.641
Oh. Hi, I'm just gonna go say hi
to to Dion.

41:58.724 --> 42:01.727
Actually, uh,
Dion's had a really long day.

42:01.810 --> 42:03.771
He's... he's really not up for company.

42:04.230 --> 42:08.067
-Well, he'll wanna see me.
-Nicole asked me not to let you see him.

42:08.150 --> 42:09.109
[scoffs]

42:09.401 --> 42:10.277
What?

42:10.694 --> 42:12.321
She doesn't want you to see him.

42:12.905 --> 42:13.822
I'm sorry.

42:13.906 --> 42:15.324
That's ridiculous. [exhales]

42:15.407 --> 42:16.617
Well, it's her choice.

42:16.700 --> 42:18.577
Okay, uh, you know what?
I want to talk to Dion.

42:18.661 --> 42:21.247
You know, why don't you just go home
and take some time?

42:21.330 --> 42:24.833
[groans in pain] You know what?
I don't have time. Okay.

42:25.584 --> 42:28.337
Nicole and I just had
a small disagreement, okay?

42:28.420 --> 42:31.757
-I'm practically the kid's father.
-Whoa. You are entitled.

42:31.840 --> 42:33.050
She called me entitled?

42:33.926 --> 42:36.595
Well, you know what? Yeah, actually,
I am entitled to see my godson,

42:36.679 --> 42:38.180
so get the hell out of my way.

42:38.430 --> 42:39.265
I...

42:39.932 --> 42:40.808
said...

42:41.225 --> 42:42.810
-[electricity crackles]
-no.

42:45.854 --> 42:46.689
[scoffing]

42:47.356 --> 42:49.358
I should have killed you in New Orleans.

42:49.775 --> 42:51.277
[electricity crackling]

42:57.491 --> 42:59.034
[electricity crackling loudly]

43:00.536 --> 43:01.370
No.

43:03.872 --> 43:05.332
[lightning crackling]

43:05.416 --> 43:06.542
[cell phone rings]

43:06.625 --> 43:07.501
Hello?

43:07.585 --> 43:08.836
-[Suzanne] <i>Where are you?</i>
-Why?

43:08.919 --> 43:11.171
There's a micro storm forming right now
at your building.

43:11.255 --> 43:14.592
-Come to BIONA. We can protect you here.
-No, no, Dion is at home.

43:16.510 --> 43:17.511
Jesus.

43:17.595 --> 43:18.679
[thunder rumbles]

43:18.762 --> 43:20.848
Come on, come on. Pick up, pick up.

43:20.931 --> 43:22.057
[thunder rumbles]

43:24.727 --> 43:25.894
[Charlotte screams]

43:30.065 --> 43:35.529
You can't have Dion!

43:35.863 --> 43:37.197
[groaning]

43:42.328 --> 43:44.455
[Charlotte groaning]

43:45.205 --> 43:46.081
[grunts]

43:46.832 --> 43:48.584
[Charlotte grunting]

43:52.254 --> 43:53.130
[Charlotte] No!

43:53.213 --> 43:56.759
[Charlotte screaming]

43:56.842 --> 43:57.676
No!

43:59.762 --> 44:02.056
[dramatic music playing]
